I would posit that Capitalism, as an economic term, is fading in usefulness in face of crypto's rearchitecture of global finance.
Sure, you can set out to get others rich. But generally speaking, capitalism is defined more by self-interest, historically speaking.
The value provided to others, via Adam Smith's invisible hand, is a corollary of self-interest. (Altruism is good too, and can add value).
